<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <base href="/" />

    @* Bootstrap still loaded during the UI-modernization migration window
       (Day 1–3). The Day-4 cleanup removes this link once every page uses
       MudBlazor components. Until then both grids coexist. *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["lib/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"]" />

    @* Typography: Inter is preferred but not fetched from the network. The
       app.css body stack falls through to `Segoe UI` / `system-ui` so the demo
       box renders cleanly even when the venue blocks external font CDNs (the
       previous Google Fonts link tripped the venue's CSP). *@

    @* MudBlazor base styles — must come AFTER Bootstrap so Mud wins specificity
       on the components that have switched over. *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="_content/MudBlazor/MudBlazor.min.css" />

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["app.css"]" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["Consensus.Web.styles.css"]" />
    <ImportMap />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="favicon.png" />

    <HeadOutlet />
</head>

<body>
    @* Render mode set at the Routes level so MainLayout (and the MudBlazor
       providers it hosts) run interactively without each page needing its
       own @rendermode declaration. Account/Login and Account/Register use
       `<EditForm data-enhance="false">` so their HTTP form POSTs continue
       to work the same whether the surrounding tree is SSR or interactive. *@
    <Routes @rendermode="InteractiveServer" />
    <script src="_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>
    <script src="_content/MudBlazor/MudBlazor.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/blazor-debug.js"></script>
    <script src="js/dashboard.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
